      "writtenOn": "2020-10-01T19:29:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Usage is basically:\nif (\u003cthis is a taskspec click\u003e) {\n  // extract info from element, look stuff up etc\n  dialog.displayTaskSpec(...);\nelse if (\u003cthis is a task click\u003e) {\n  ...\n} else if (\u003cthis is a commit click) {\n  ...\n} else {\n  dialog.close()\n}\n\nI opted for the single element for a few reasons:\n--the existing/previous task-popup-sk and others are mostly just copy paste of each other and intentionally look consistent.  If we altered the look of one we\u0027d likely want to do it for all 3.\n--They are all used in a single place, so we don\u0027t need modularity.\n--it slightly simplifies calling code, since you don\u0027t have to do \"open X, but first close Y and Z, if they\u0027re open\" type stuff.",
